dct_title_s: [De Zuyd Zee of Mer Du Sud]
dct_description_sm: California as an island on second Sanson model, with indented northern coast and coastal place names. "Straet Anian" to north. "Staten Landt" (also called "Nouvelle Zeelande of Nieu Zeeland") to far southwest. "Compagnies Land" to northwest now has completed coastline. "de Eylanden van Salomon" are added. Gerard van Keulen carried on the work of his father, Johannes van Keulen, and managed the House of Van Keulen from 1704-1727. Charts did not appear with his name prior to this time. Similar to J. van Keulen's map of 1680 and Robijn's map of 1683.
"Tot Amsterdam by Gerard van Keulen. Aan de Nieuwe brug. Met Previlegie"
